ce:section.ce:para:
To evaluate the practicability of the sensor for the detecting ClO− and Cu2+, tap water and lake water were selected for further analysis. The concentrations of the above two ions were determined by standard addition method. Table 1
                         demonstrated the recoveries of ClO− in tap water and lake water were 99.29 %−102.2 % and 99.29 %−105.7 % respectively, with relative standard deviations (RSD) less than 0.77 %. Similarly, the recoveries of Cu2+ detection using CDs-ClO− system and RSD were satisfactory (Table 2
                        ). In summary, the designed ratiometric fluorescent sensor had potential application value for the actual detection of ClO− and Cu2+.
